cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   The first Defence we're going to look at is a defence to Pre-empts.

I would guess that most of you just double for take-out, anything else is natural and that's about it.

Indeed that's how *I* play most of the time.

However just occasionally, you might find yourself in a situation where Opps are vulnerable and you are not. 

They pre-empt, and you're sat with a trump stack and a biggish hand and would REALLY like to be able to double for penalties.

If that's the case then FILM-X is the convention for you!!! 


FILM-X is a combination of two different defences to Pre-empts: "FIshbein", and "Lower Minor".

^c^*bFishbein^*n     ^g NEXT SUIT UP  over a pre-empt is for  Takeout.
|n^|5|at|
^c^*bLower-Minor^*n  ^g cheapest  MINOR  suit over the pre-empt is for  Takeout.


The combined scheme for FILM-X is as follows:|
